review_text: The packaging is very pretty, it comes with a doe foot applicator and the product is fragrance free. The consistency is thin but the pigmentation is there but to a not point where you get overwhelmed because it a metallic liquid lipstick even there is mettaticness to the product but it's very Sophisticated and looks good overall. But the product is drying on the lips but nothing a lip primer or a lip balm cannot solve. Now coming to eyes. It applied beautifully no patchiness whatsoever blended beautifully with finger as well as brush, layering was also easy and the best part it didn't crease. I have hooded oily eyelids even Powder shadow creases on me but this being a liquid performed nicely, it stayed for around 4hrs without creasing, that is like a very good staying power for a liquid product. I guess that's a reason it's drying on the lips because the product sets. Overall a nice product for the price

review_text: I'll go Cons first then the Pros- Cons: 1. The cap and the bottom outer part of the lipstick are made of paper stock which is obviously not sturdy at all and runs the risk of getting ruined in case of contact with water. 2. With the inner plastic part/s the packaging is not completely biodegradable. So the paper stock outer shell has no purpose apart from lowering the manufacturing cost. 3. The retail price is 599, which is too high to get a paper stock outer shell and no ingredients mentioned anywhere (so we cannot even be sure that we're getting a high-quality lipstick). Pros: 1. The package is very eye-catching. 2. The creamy matte texture does not crack your lips(if you have droughty lips like mine, you might wanna prep your lips with a thick lip balm before). 3. Adding lip balm or lip gloss won't disrupt the consistency of its pigment. 4. Can be applied with light taps on the lips for a subtle nude finish and can be built up for color intensity. 5. Can be worn both for everyday office look or evening party looks.
